I am in quite a small guild of RL friends, yes, we might not have the gear of BotS, we might not have 200 people.  But we get the job done with 20 people or less.  We exp group in PoS when BoT and PoV is filled up, 1 group, sometimes 4 people even less, and we have little to no problems.  Now because we are a smaller guild, killing a mob like Grummus and Terris Thule is pretty much impossible for us, but dammit we will try.  We have a couple tanks with 7-8k hp and 100 ish aa's I myself full raid buffed have about 6000hp - not the best, but not like I am in a guild that can goto nToV whenever I want.  In BoT we can non-stop pull for hours and hours even with named popping in between all the pulls, and still soon as named dies, we are ready to pull another.  Does this make us less of a guild because we don't have zerg forces?  People sometimes forget the game is not all about how many people you can get, but the skills of the people playing the characters.<br>
<br>
Yes, we often have hard times with certain mobs, we have yet to kill Vindi.  My wizard went LD at 50% and my stepdad went LD who was a rotation cleric same time I did.  And we lost at 2%.  Yeah it sucked, but hey, shit happens.  But you can bet we are capable of killing him.  We often don't have a lot of people to do this stuff, most the time in guildchat we have about 10 people max.  We would like to see the other PoP zones, and if we have to join another guild on a flag raid then so be it.  We all paid for the expansion as well.  Even if we don't see in CoD all day, at least we know when we have enough people online we can go if we want and screw around and have some fun.  Yes, omg I said fun.  Go figure, wtf does that word mean?<br>
<br>
