<br>
ANY mob can be a rotation mob.  All it takes is:<br>
<br>
1) for there to be two or more groups (guild/alliance) wanting access to it for some reason (epic pieces is a good example - and yes, folks used to post when they were going after the reavers in CoM in advance).<br>
2) it makes sense - obviously, multi-day spawn mobs fit the bill.  mobs that spawn every 30 minutes do not make sense to form a rotation on<br>
<br>
<br>
And, if you want to be picky about wording, it means that any mob is eligible for a rotation if two or more parties want it to be.  The fact that it isn't on the web page does not mean that a rotation cannot be requested on it if/when someone wants. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=emilsinclair>Emil Sinclair</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 371<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(3/3/03 8:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=534.topic&index=229>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Teamwork</span><hr size=1> one thing i will add, regarding pocket's comments on the above mobs.<br>
<br>
(Talendor, Gorenaire, Phingil Atropos, Black Reavers, any mob that drops an Epic piece)<br>
<br>
All of these mobs can be single grped (or less).  It is just nearly impossible to enforce a rotation on these types of mobs.  This issue came up with lodi.  People even wanted him on a rot (which i neither was for nor against), but being practical -- when a mob is killable with a single group or so, it is simply impossible to enforce anything on it, really.  Who knows how many subscribers play on the rathe?  3k, 5k?? i have no idea.. and of those, how many actually browse this board, etc.<br>
<br>
While in theory, these types of mobs could go to rotation, should somone request it, enforcing it would be very nearly impossible.<br>
<br>
Regarding Sontalak, there are 5 (more now due to the kael additions) avenues to ST.  The 5 first brood.  Sontalak is the most difficult of the 5, which is probably the major factor in him never making rotation status. (inherent laziness of us all!).<br>
<br>
I can assure you if sontalak was the only means to ST, he would be on a rotation to this day.<br>
<br>
Comparing sontalak to behe is flawed, imo.  I would compare sontalak to the quest to enter potac/cod/hoh, an alternate means (albeit sont is 'harder' in actual encounter difficulty, the quest is 'harder' because it takes longer and only yields 1 flag per completion) to enter a zone.  The quest mobs to enter potac, cod, hoh are not on rotations either -- even though they are rare spawns and so forth.<br>
